metadata.name: Mental Lines #29
metadata.description:
To challenge a mind, the lines are arranged randomly and at different angles to show a mental creativity.
We usually draw these lines and drawings when we are anxious or bored. As a result, we often paint these shapes without full awareness, resulting in our mental preoccupations showing through.
Drawing with mixed lines, requires patience and perseverance. Additionally, mood swings are prone to be triggered by these images.
Convoluted lines are often drawn by people who are a little obsessive about their decisions and loved ones. In most cases, such pictures are drawn by introverted people.
Made by p5.js

press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: Take Wing #86
metadata.description:
‚ÄúTake Wing‚Äù is a generative art collection depicting the hope, optimism, and thrilling excitement of a person taking off, gaining traction, and soaring to new heights and off into the great unknown.  

The algorithm behind the piece stems from an attempt to go back to art fundamentals and codify composition rules and painterly techniques into a generative form - taking into account focal points, contrast, eye movement, and color theory while still giving the algorithm freedom to explore random color palettes, random flow field movement, random brush strokes, and many other degrees of freedom.

The collection is made in pure code with p5.js and a few GLSL fragment shaders.

The piece has been created to be exhibited at "In Touch" with VerticalCryptoArt in Berlin in September 2022, curated by Anika Meier.

------------------------------------------------

To get a (somewhat) high-resolution output, open the live view of your token, and then edit the URL adding &h=5400 at the end of it.  5400 is the tallest you can go, but you can also put a smaller number if you desire.  Be aware that this will only work on a machine with a very beefy GPU, and even then may take a bit, so please be patient!

metadata.name: The Samsara-Verse #20
metadata.description:
Samsara is the endless Wheel of Life, where uncountable numbers of souls ceaselessly wander through its 6 realms - Deva-gati (abode of the gods), Asura-gati (demi-gods), Preta-gati (hungry ghosts), Naraka-gati (Hell), Tiryagyoni-gati (animals), Manusya-gati (the human realm).
 
These realms are interleaved with manifold planes of existence separated by the thinnest of veils.
And yet - these hives of endless activity are but a small fraction of the totality of the metaverse, as multitudes of unformed universes, as yet mere sketches, await their blooming.

This artwork consists of both a visual aspect and a sonic representation echoing the voices of the denizens of the various planes of the Samsara-Verse.

Once the piece has finished drawing, click or press "m" to unmute the soundtrack.
Press "s" to save the image as a ".png" file (4800x3600 pixels).

Collaborative work by Geoffrey Crayon - art design and coding - and Cylonix (JJClark) - sound design. The audio samples used (in addition to generative drones) are from Loopology and Splice.

metadata.name: COMPUTERS #17
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from pixel array computations and classic noise algorithms.

COMPUTERS is a meditation on the aesthetics of computing in all of its forms. It recalls the types of computation required to build temples, write complex texts, weave detailed textiles, and program computer games. Pixels have always existed in some form or another, before and after the screen. Every iteration of COMPUTERS suggests that computation is both contemporary and ancient.

Press 'p' or click to pause the animation.
Press 's' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: Constellation Builder 02 #8
metadata.description:
As particles approach one another, interconnections form leading to larger constellation systems.

Based on an earlier project on Polygon
inspired by #genuary2022 prompt

Mouse/Trackpad:
drag -> camera rotation
Mouse Rt Btn -> camera pan
scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

p: screen capture

Built with three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

Thank you for endless support and love:  Robin, Ian, Sophie, Hilary and Eric
In Memory: Jerry (Dad)

metadata.name: STRANGE LANDS #33
metadata.description:
Flying over the earth the land deforms warped by speed and geology. Columns of light rise from the land distorting earth and sky. 

STRANGE LANDS

- 7 Color Palettes
- 2 Aspect Ratios
- 6 Wave Distortions
- 5 Levels of Color Filling
- 2 Stroke Variants
- 4 Fill Styles

STRANGE LANDS Commands

Press S to save as an SVG

Image outputs on non mobile devices can be saved in high resolution PNG format by simply right-click saving.
